data.title: Keith Scott

data.text: Keith Scott built up his experience by exercising his vocal roles in an array of different films. In his early voice career, Scott worked in animated films like "Dot and Keeto" (1985), "Dot and the Koala" (1985) and "Dot and the Whale" (1985). After that, Scott moved on to lend his vocal talents for roles in films like "The Magic Riddle" (1991) and "Blinky Bill" (1992). In addition to his voice work, he appeared on camera in the Brendan Fraser smash hit comedy adventure "George of the Jungle" (1997). Scott continued to exercise his talent in the nineties, taking on a mix of projects like "Paws" (HBO, 1998-99), "Fractured Fairy Tales: The Phox, The Box & The Lox" (1999) and "The War Zone" (1999). Scott most recently worked on the Rene Russo animated adventure "The Adventures of Rocky and Bullwinkle" (2000).
